<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11243015-elias"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1438461814i/11243015._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11243015-elias">Elias</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This would make for one hell of a movie. I disliked Blood Red Road (or Dust Lands: Blood Red Road, as it&apos;s now called) because I absolutely loathed Mo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This would make for one hell of a movie. I disliked Blood Red Road (or Dust Lands: Blood Red Road, as it's now called) because I absolutely loathed Moira Young's writing. I hated the constant (intentional, I think) typos and lack of quotations and all the fragments. However, I thought that the story and characters were terrific. I would love to see this thrilling, gripping story played out on the big screen, or on TV, or anywhere without all those typos.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
